The panel popped open on a simple hinge, revealing layer upon layer of insulatio
n, metal and radiation shielding.
 Though radiation-hardened, the machines which designed the orbiting factories
 opted for triple-redundancy.
 Even meteor impacts up to a certain degree could be tolerated, the manufactorie
s shutting off certain refinement lines and keeping the rest open and working.
 The cost was easily absorbed; the money pouring in from the belt had been
 unprecedented.
 The term Goldilock's zone had once been reserved for the sweet spot in
 a planet's orbit around its star that made it hospitable to humans.
 Now, it was the asteroid's belt colloquial name.
