He repeated the same mantra over and over, as he tried to contact the maintenanc
e station.
 There had been no near-object scans for that particular sector, no sudden
 warning shifts.
 Whatever hit the pod, wasn't supposed to be there.
 Everything had gone terribly wrong, and a single thought occupied Khalid's
 mind: be with God, and do not fear.
